        "id": "3f35500b711a985b",
        "text": "I love studying people. I’ve probably done it all my life but perhaps only became conscious of it in my late teens, even considering studying psychology at university. I like hypothesising what others might be thinking, how they’re feeling. I notice the way they talk and the gestures they make, fancying myself as someone who can ‘read’ people. I often consider interactions days after they’ve occurred, perhaps to gain some deeper understanding. Classic overthinker. I consider this self-proclaimed skill both a blessing and a curse – but mostly a blessing. Particularly when it comes to my job. "
      },
      "date": 1641433201565
    },
